Name: familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia 1
Definition: A familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia that has_material_basis_in heterozygous loss-of-function mutations in the CASR gene on chromosome 3q21.

Name: familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia 2
Definition: A familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GNA11 gene on chromosome 19p13.

Name: familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia 3
Definition: A familial hypocalciuric hypercalcemia that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the AP2S1 gene on chromosome 19q13.
